::Cygnar::
       He smiles.  He was finally in his element.  "With all due respect Lord 
Galvatron, I am the tactician here not you.  I believe that is why you've 
kept me around so long."  He shakes his head calling up a map of the area 
around the tripred base.  "No, I think our interests will best be served by 
hiding until the battle is drawing to a close.  We need to make sure that 
most of the forces are down by the time we enter.  Otherwise they'll surround 
you sir.  And I seriously doubt you can take on one much less two factions of 
bots.  Even with our help they'd concentrate mostly on you.  You'd go down 
and we'd be leaderless.  That's bad for morale."

--part1_a5.2c15b44e.2a907557_boundary
